          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A system capability change is a system level transition from a set of system capabilities to a new set of system capabilities. Power management sends a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "kIOMessageSystemCapabilityChange",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " message and provides this structure as the message data (by reference) to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "gIOPriorityPowerStateInterest",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " clients when system capability changes.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
